com.ndi

Class EnumFormatValidator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ndi.EnumFormatValidator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    org.everit.json.schema.FormatValidator

    public class EnumFormatValidator
extends java.lang.Object
implements org.everit.json.schema.FormatValidator
    A very flexible customized format option validator. It allows user to creates format tag that is not present in the Json Schema Official Specification. This validator can be used when we want to restrict an entry to a set of predefined values, but at the same time, when the user has entered another set of value, we want to create suggestions for the user to enter the correct values. It extends the FormatValidator class, which is called by the Everit Validator when it encounters the this user's defined format tag in the schema document Example usage: EnumFormatValidator.Builder builder = new EnumFormatValidator.Builder() .setTableFormat(new TableFormat().addFormat(new String[]{"\t", "\t", "\t"}) .addEntryPattern(2, ", ") .addEntryPattern(3, ", ")) .setFilePath("src/main/resources/GenBankControlledVocabulary.tsv.gz") .setRules(new Rules().addExpectedColumn(Arrays.asList("Scientific_Name", "Synonyms")) .addSuggestedColumn(Collections.singletonList("Other_Common_Name"))) .setFormatTag("animal_subject"); FormatValidator fv = builder.build(); System.out.println(fv.validate("cat")); Print out the following in the console: Optional[Entered: cat. Expected: any one of [Felis catus, Felis domesticus, Felis silvestris catus]]

      • gzipSearch

        private java.lang.String gzipSearch(java.lang.String subject)
                             throws java.io.IOException
        Perform a one-time linear search for a given entries from a gzip file. Return error message if the input is not found, return null if the input is found, return the expected input if input comes from one of the columns that are the values of the "suggestions" key in the rules' HashMap
        Parameters:
        subject - the user's input, which will be validated
        Returns:
        error message if nothing is found, null if the input is valid, expected input if the input comes from another columns of the table
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - throw IOException if file can not be found or the file becomes corrupted
